Yehud-Monosson (formerly: Yehud , Neve Monosson ) is a city in the eastern Ono Valley in the Central District . The city received its name as part of the unification of local authorities of the city of Yehud and the adjacent local council , Neve Ephraim (Neve Monosson) in 2003 . The union agreement stipulates that Neve Monosson will continue to maintain its autonomy and community uniqueness through a local administration in the statutory status of an urban district committee .